<HEADLINE>
LAKERS EYE MAGIC'S AMAECHI
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL SEGUNDO - The Lakers' search for frontcourt help has taken
them to a familiar source: the roster of the Orlando Magic. Four
years after plucking away Shaquille O'Neal, the Lakers have set
their sights on Orlando free agent John Amaechi.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-10, 270-pound Amaechi could fill two glaring Laker needs _
a backup center for O'Neal and a starter at power forward. Amaechi,
29, averaged 10.5 points and 3.3 rebounds in 80 games at center
last season, his first with Orlando.
</P>
<P>
   Amaechi met with Laker officials over the weekend but is said to
be leaning toward returning to the Magic.
</P>
<P>
   Agent Bill Sweek said 17 teams have expressed interest.
</P>
<P>
   ``At the moment, it's between the Lakers and Orlando,'' Amaechi
told the Orlando Sentinel.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers, who are over the salary cap, can only offer the
midlevel salary exception - a starting salary of $2.25 million, or
up to a six-year deal worth $17.7 million. The Magic is under the
cap and can offer Amaechi much more. Orlando also is eager to
retain him after losing its bid to land San Antonio's Tim Duncan.
</P>
<P>
   Amaechi plans to meet with Magic officials later this week
before making a decision. The Chicago Bulls, who have plenty of cap
room, also could offer Amaechi a more lucrative deal.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers also are expected to announce soon that they will
exercise their option to bring back 36-year-old guard Ron Harper.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
