<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ In the arsenal of rights
bequeathed to us by the Constitution to encourage broader
participation in our democracy, none is more valuable than the
right to vote. Unfortunately not enough of us exercise that right.
In the last presidential election, the turnout of eligible voters
was just 49 percent. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
</P>
</TEXT>
