mention his Republican rival by name, but notes that some people
seem to have developed an interest in the NAACP more recently than
others. ``I'm not asking you to read my lips. I'm asking you to
read my heart,'' Gore tells the crowd. Texas Gov. George W. Bush,
the Republican presidential hopeful, spoke to the organization on
Monday. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-GOP (Austin, Texas) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush tells
Republicans he is confident about winning the presidential race,
citing polls that show him leading Vice President Al Gore. But Bush
warns the party faithful meeting in Texas that he ``is taking
nothing for granted'' in a contest that is months away. By R.G.
RATCLIFFE.
</P>
