day, researchers in South Africa demand that the government
immediately begin providing anti-AIDS drugs to pregnant women,
arguing that such a program could prevent thousands of new
infections every year. This issue has been the overriding
controversial theme of the contentious 13th International AIDS
Conference here. By LEIGH HOPPER.
