<P>
   ANTHRAX-VACCINE (Washington) _ In unusually blunt language,
Pentagon officials Wednesday acknowledged the failure of their
ambitious policy to inoculate all military personnel against the
deadly anthrax virus. A group of government witnesses described for
lawmakers blunder after blunder in the Pentagon's two-and-a-half
year program, most dramatically a severe shortage of the vaccine
because of the mismanagement and financial problems of the only
company in the country licensed to make it, a firm that lists a
former chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff as holding an 11
percent interest. By Elaine Sciolino.
