<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Nutty Professor II' soundtrack makes the grade
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Well, it's only fitting that a movie featuring Eddie Murphy
playing more than one character would have an accompanying
soundtrack of rappers and singers taking on different _ and often
flattering _ roles.
</P>
<P>
   Balladeer Brian McKnight does a Babyface imitation on ``Thinkin'
Bout Me,'' a left-at-the-altar lament that shares the building song
structure, lush arrangement and yearning of Face's standards. (The
difference being Babyface probably wouldn't do a cocky song
claiming his ex-girlfriend is thinking about him while she's with
her new husband.)
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta producers Tim &AMP; Bob drop gritty vocalist Case into a
swirl of strings and elegance on ``Missing You,'' the kind of
backdrop usually associated with McKnight or Joe.
</P>
<P>
   And artist Musiq introduces himself on ``Just Friends (Sunny)''
by wrapping himself in the warm keyboards and coolness of D'Angelo
_ minus a little of D'Angelo's smoothness. But the scene snatchers
are Jay-Z's charismatic boast ``Hey Papi'' and Redman &AMP; Eminem's
rugged and appropriately titled ``Off the Wall.'' Both earn the
starring role of lead single that Janet Jackson holds, and lazily
portrays, on the airy collection of coos called ``Doesn't Really
Matter.'' Rightly so.
</P>
<P>
   `Nutty Professor II' soundtrack
</P>
<P>
   Various artists. Def Jam/Def Soul. 16 tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _Sonia Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : More on Nutty Professor and Def Jam Records:
www.nuttyprofessor.com
</P>
<P>
   www.defjam.com.
</P>
