   DEATH-TAX (Washington) _ In the wake of accusations of a
``do-nothing'' Congress, Republican leaders on Capitol Hill are
focused this week on passing two significant bills: a repeal of the
marriage tax, which penalizes some married couples, and a revision
of the death tax, which is now imposed on people who inherit large
estates. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1000 words.
</P>
