   GENO-HYPE (Undated) _ Seeking to puncture ``geno-hype,'' a New
England Journal of Medicine article says the potential of genomics
to ``revolutinize medicine'' by testing people for a lifetime of
disease risks is overblown and may never come to pass. By Richard
Saltus. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   NH-IMPEACH (Concord, N.H.) _ With three unprecendented votes in
New Hampshire history, the House approves all three impeachment
articles against Supreme Court Chief Justice David A. Brock. Unless
he resigns first, Brock will face a Senate trial -- New Hampshire's
first in 210 years. By Lois Shea. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BOSTON-SCIENTIFIC (Undated) _ Boston Scientific is cutting 850
jobs and transfering another 900 to Miami and Ireland in an attempt
to increase productivity. By Ronald Rosenberg. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-COLLEGE (Boston) _ UPromise Inc., backed by some big names
and even bigger money, intends to create a network of companies
that give rebates by kicking dollars toward individual college
savings accounts. By Scott Bernard Nelson. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   TOYSMART-LIST (Undated) _ Bankrupt Toysmart.com is trying to
reach a settlement with the FTC by offering to sell its customer
list to Walt Disney Co., its majority shareholder. By Stephanie
Stoughton. 650 words.
