r d BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX     07-12 0908
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EGGPLANT FROM THE GARDEN GETS THE FULL TREATMENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Beryl Scroggins has a good memory.
</P>
<P>
   She remembered that several years ago we ran a recipe for the
baked eggplant served at Wyatt's cafeterias. Now that her son is
growing eggplant in his garden, she needs the recipe.
</P>
<P>
   Yes, indeed, we did run that recipe along with several others
from Wyatt's in 1993. So here's the eggplant recipe, along with a
couple of other Wyatt's concoctions to round out a vegetable plate.
Please note that the cheese sauce is used in both the spinach and
the squash recipe.
</P>
<P>
   WYATT'S BAKED EGGPLANT &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 pound eggplant, peeled &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 pound dry bread, cubed &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup canned evaporated milk &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup whole milk &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup butter, melted &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup onions, finely chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup green bell pepper, finely chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup celery, finely chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 eggs, slightly beaten &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon pimento, chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon sage &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, grated &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salted water
in refrigerator overnight (minimum 6 hours). Drain eggplant and
place in pan. Cover with water and simmer until tender. Soak bread
cubes in milk. Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in melted
butter for about 15 minutes or until tender.
</P>
<P>
   Combine cooked eggplant, bread cubes and sauteed vegetables. Add
eggs, pimento and seasonings; blend thoroughly. Place in greased
baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Top with grated
cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 358 calories, 22 grams fat, 27
grams carbohydrates, 15 grams protein, 129 milligrams cholesterol,
1,284 milligrams sodium, 54 percent of calories from fat. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WYATT'S SPINACH SUPREME &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8-10 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 (10 ounces each) boxes frozen chopped spinach, thawed &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup bread crumbs &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons margarine, melted &QL;
</P>
<P>
   4 slices uncooked bacon, cut in half &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cheese sauce, recipe follows &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Place thawed spinach in pot of boiling salted water. Return to
boil, then simmer for 10 minutes. Drain in colander; squeeze out
excess moisture.
</P>
<P>
   Combine cheese sauce recipe with cooked and drained spinach.
Place in casserole dish.
</P>
<P>
   Combine melted margarine and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over top of
spinach mixture. Place bacon slices on top of spinach. Bake at 350
degrees for 20 to 30 minutes, or just until done.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 210 calories, 15 grams fat, 12
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 23 milligrams cholesterol,
652 milligrams sodium, 63 percent of calories from fat. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WYATT'S CHEESE SAUCE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Yields 4 cups &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 ounces margarine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup flour &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 cups warm milk &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3/4 teaspoon paprika &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup Cheez Whiz &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Melt margarine, whisking in flour. Cook for 3 minutes.
Continuing to whisk, add warm milk. Bring to boil, stirring
constantly to make smooth.
</P>
<P>
   Add salt, pepper, paprika and Cheez Whiz. Stir until all Cheez
Whiz is completely melted.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 45 calories, 3 grams fat, 2
grams carbohydrates, 2 grams protein, 6 milligrams cholesterol, 155
milligrams sodium, 67 percent of calories from fat. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WYATT'S CREAMED SQUASH &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Serves 12 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   4 pounds yellow squash, washed, stemmed and cut into 1/4-inch
slices &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons margarine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 pound onion, finely chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 pound green bell pepper, finely chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 scallions, diced &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon jalapeno pepper mix, recipe follows &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon sugar &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Cheese sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 corn tortillas, see note &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 ounces Cheddar cheese, grated &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Note: Cut tortillas in quarters and deep-fry in vegetable oil.
Dump fried chips onto sheet pan covered with paper towels and
sprinkle with salt while still wet with oil.
</P>
<P>
   Jalapeno pepper mix: Combine crushed jalapeno peppers, diced
pimentos, finely chopped onions and jalapeno pepper juice.
</P>
<P>
   Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until clear. Add
jalapeno mix, scallions, salt, sugar, pepper and cheese sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Steam squash for 5 minutes. Add to onion mixture and mix gently.
</P>
<P>
   Lightly coat inside of serving pans with melted shortening. Put
squash mixture into serving pans and bake at 350 degrees for 15
minutes. Top with grated cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Place one of the fried tortilla quarters on top of each serving.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 89 calories, 4 grams fat, 11
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 5 milligrams cholesterol, 59
milligrams sodium, 40 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   Request:
</P>
<P>
   Margaret Carrof Fort Worth has misplaced her favorite zucchini
recipe. She says the zucchini halves were hollowed out and filled,
she believes with cottage cheese and tomatoes, and she also thinks
the dish was microwaved.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)  &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
