<P>
   ``And then he looked down and he read the first photograph, and
he called out the name of his granddaughter,'' Carter said. ``And
then one by one he read out the names of his grandchildren. And
tears ran down his cheeks. And, when I saw them, I also cried. And
he said, 'Why don't we try one more time.'''
</P>
<P>
   Said Carter, ''To make a long story short, we concluded the
agreement.''
</P>
<P>
   (Bob Deans' E-mail address is: bobdeans(at)coxnews.com)
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
