<HEADER>
A0318 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e BC-X-MEN-GUIDE-LADN &LR;      07-12 1032
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-X-MEN-GUIDE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A GUIDE TO THE MUTANTS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GLENN WHIPP 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Don't know your ``X-Men'' from your ``X-Files''? Don't feel bad.
None of the actors involved in the big-screen adaptation of the
popular Marvel comic book series had a clue about their film's
hand-drawn source material, either.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not like I'm spending much time at the neighborhood comic
books store,'' sniffs Ian McKellen, who plays the movie's evil
ringleader.
</P>
<P>
   It's likely you aren't either. A brief explanation, then: The
X-men (and women) are mutant human beings who possess extraordinary
abilities _ telepathy, physical strength, agility and the like.
Many consider the X-men freaks, including U.S. Senator Robert Kelly
(Bruce Davison), who leads a McCarthy-type witch hunt to ``expose
the dangers'' of mutants.
</P>
<P>
   Mutant leader Professor X (Patrick Stewart) still believes
mutants and ``normal'' humans can get along. His nemesis, Magneto
(McKellen), thinks otherwise, and wants to crush the humans before
they suppress the mutants.
</P>
<P>
   Use the following scorecard to help keep the heroes and villains
properly sorted.
</P>
<P>
   MUTANTS WHO LIKE HUMANS
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Professor X
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Patrick Stewart
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Wheelchair-bound mutant scientist who tutors
``gifted'' students to use their superhuman powers for the good of
mankind. A powerful telepath himself, Professor X clashes
philosophically with old friend Magneto over whether mutants and
humans can ever co-exist.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``My career has been littered with kings,
captains, emperors, party bosses, trade union leaders, presidents,
generals; you name it, I've worn the uniform. What's truly ironic
is that I am the least authoritarian figure you're ever likely to
meet.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Wolverine
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Hugh Jackman
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Fan favorite, a lupine loner who possesses
superhuman senses of sight, smell and hearing, as well as the
ability to heal himself. His skeleton is unbreakable; his claws can
slash through steel.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``Hard-core fans are wondering how some Aussie
with a musical theater background can play Wolverine. Two words:
Cold showers. We filmed in Toronto in the middle of winter, so a
cold shower at 5:30 in the morning will make you very, very angry.
Any time I thought about it during the day, it put me in character.
It's like eating a lemon.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Storm
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Halle Berry
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Comes from a line of African witch-priestesses who
can control the weather. Al Roker's dream date.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``Storm is connected to the earth, so it's
natural that she's the earth mother of the team. But while she's
sensitive and all, she still kicks a little butt. I liked that.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Cyclops
</P>
<P>
   Actor: James Marsden
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: The squarest of the X-men, but that's not why he
wears the glasses. Cyclops' eyes release a laser beam that can cut
through practically anything.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``The audience never sees Cyclops' eyes, which
makes conveying emotion a little difficult. I did a lot of eyebrow
work.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Jean Grey
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Famke Janssen
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: A telepath to rival Professor X, Jean Grey can also
make the earth move _ as well as any other object, large or small _
with her mind. She also has caught the eye of both Wolverine and
Cyclops, probably as much for the way she looks in leather as for
her superhuman talents.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``I'm no mind reader, but I'd love to have the
talent. Then I could tell when somebody in Hollywood is bull----ing
me.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant Rogue
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Anna Paquin
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Alienated teen is a storehouse of talents and
memories, which she absorbs from anyone she touches. This makes it
hard for her to live a normal adolescent life, much less kiss a
date on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``There's no way I could turn down a chance to
be in a movie with Ian McKellen and Patrick Stewart. Plus, coming
from a comic book makes the character research pretty easy.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MUTANTS WHO WANT TO CRUSH HUMANS
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Magneto
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Ian McKellen
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Auschwitz internment as a youngster colors his view
of humanity. Believes the only good human is a dead human and
carries out his credo in attempt to establish mutant rule over
earth. As name implies, he has both a magnetic personality and
power over people.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``Being a gay man, I could relate to the
story's themes of intolerance. Society, by its laws and attitudes,
often makes me feel like I'm a mutant.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Sabretooth
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Tyler Mane
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Wolverine's hated enemy, which makes this the
series' Luke Skywalker/Darth Vader relationship, since the 7-foot-2
Sabretooth might be Wolverine's father. Like Wolverine, he has
extraordinary sight, smell and strength, abilities he uses to
satisfy his rage against mankind.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``Having been a wrestler made the stunts a
little easier, although I had to adapt my body-slam style into more
of a slasher thing. But this character was a piece of cake. I
played wrestling villains that would make Sabretooth look like
Lassie.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Mystique
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Rebecca Romijn-Stamos
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Superhuman chameleon can transform herself into
anything or anyone. But because she's played by Sports Illustrated
swimsuit cover girl Romijn-Stamos, Mystique usually goes for the
skin-tight blue leather ensemble.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself ``I'm just used to having six people hovering
over me for a photo shoot, so these 10-hour make-up days were just
more of the same. You just go to this Zen place of mindlessness
where you turn off your brain.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mutant: Toad
</P>
<P>
   Actor: Ray Park
</P>
<P>
   X-planation: Toad jumps when Magneto speaks, and his 12-foot
projectile tongue comes in handy for more than licking stamps.
</P>
<P>
   X-press yourself: ``Once I had green skin and green hair and
warts on my face and I was driving home from the set. I was
starving and stopped at Subway, and the guy felt a little pity for
me and gave me extra helpings on my sandwich.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
