<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, July 13 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   DNC-PROTEST (Los Angeles) _ Organizers of the protest for the
Democratic National Convention issue a ``call to action'' for
volunteers, demanding an end to ``corporate profits over human
need.'' Could this be a taste of things to come? By Erik Nelson.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BADDRIVERS (Los Angeles) _ California ranks fourth nationwide
for motorists with suspended licenses involved in fatal crashes,
and nearly 6 percent of Los Angeles County drivers have suspended
licenses, according to a new study by the AAA Foundation for
Traffic Safety. The study shows that when drivers' licenses are
suspended or revoked, drivers often continue to drive -- with
potentially deadly consequences. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-12-00 1906EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000712.0281 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
