   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   KING-CBS (Atlanta) _ In exchange for a cash payment, the estate
of the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. dropped its lawsuit
Wednesday against CBS News over the rights to King's 1963
masterwork, the ``I Have a Dream'' speech. (Summary from wires) By
David Firestone. (540 words)
</P>
<P>
   COLO-WILDFLOWER-TOURS (Mount Crested Butte, Colo.) _ A little
idea to bring tourists and money into a small ski resort during the
summer has grown beyond expectations. Wildflower tours of the
Rockies from Mount Crested Butte have become so popular, they're
turning people away. By Michael Janofsky. (1000 words)
</P>
