<P>
   NY-BLAST (New York) _ A body was discovered Wednesday beneath
four feet of rubble in a pair of collapsed Brooklyn buildings where
two other people were feared trapped, Mayor Rudy Giuliani said. The
search effort will likely continue into the night, he said.
According to the mayor, authorities now believe a gas explosion was
likely to blame for the Tuesday night explosion, although the
investigation was continuing. By David Barstow.
