</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: For a few years, I have been using Memories of Kobe
(Souvenirs de Kobe) made by President's Choice (PC) as a marinade
for steaks and chicken. Suddenly, it disappeared. Everyone I have
introduced Kobe to has fallen in love with its tangy flavor, which
will make even the most discriminating mouths water. I was able to
find it in Canada last summer because PC is made there.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dan Gimbert, Dunwoody , Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Your memory of this sauce serves you well. The Oriental-style
tamari garlic marinade is available in select sites in the States,
for example, Jewel food stores in the Chicago area, but it is not
available in Georgia; however, you can order it through President's
Choice International in Canada. Twelve bottles (each 350
milligrams) are about $32.50. Use a credit card for easy payment.
Information: 1-416-750-7203 or www.pcbaskets.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I bought Tarn-X, a liquid silver tarnish remover, at the old
Roses stores, and now I can't find it. The remover came in a black
and white 12-ounce plastic bottle. Is it available in metro
Atlanta?
</P>
<P>
   _ Killian Smith, Decatur, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We couldn't tarnish our reputation for finding hard-to-find
items and not find this one. You can buy Tarn-X (12-ounce bottle,
$5.29) at Walgreens, 5455 Lawrenceville Highway, Lilburn
(770-381-8582). Polish the family's sterling with this remover as
well as items in silver plate, platinum, copper and gold. However,
do not use on stainless steel, chrome, pewter, aluminum, brass,
lacquered surfaces, pearls or porous stones.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for the clear gel sunscreen PreSun SPF 30. I
used to buy it at Kroger but I can't find it there anymore.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dot Hale, Tucker, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   And another PreSun request: My dermatologist tells me to buy
PreSun Ultra Sunscreen for the most effective sun protection. It is
recommended by the Skin Cancer Foundation and made by Bristol-Myers
Squibb Co. But I'm having trouble finding it. Can you find out what
pharmacies might carry it?
</P>
<P>
   _ Brad Wolverton, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   Yet another sunscreen request: At my daughter-in-law's request,
I am trying to find Bull Frog Sunblock for Kids. No one seems to
have it this year.
</P>
<P>
   _ Betty Frame, Lilburn, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Kids of all ages need protection when going out in the sun.
We found both PreSun Ultra Sunscreen SPF 30 (4-ounce gel or cream
$8.99) and Bull Frog Sunblock for Kids (4-ounce gel, $9.99) at
Eckerd Drugs, 2325 Pleasant Hill Road, Duluth (770-497-4425).
PreSun contains Parsol 1789, which protects you from both UVA rays
responsible for wrinkling skin and UVB rays that cause sunburn. The
Bull Frog bottle has a neat green frog cap that will appeal to
youngsters, and the gel offers all-day UVA/UVB protection. The gel
smells like watermelon.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I have been trying to locate Ralston 100% Wheat Hot Cereal
since I moved back to Atlanta in early '99. Made by Ralston Foods,
a division of Ralcorp Holdings Inc. of St. Louis, the cereal comes
in a yellow and brown box. Any information would be appreciated.
</P>
<P>
   _ Thomas F. Moran, Suwanee, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Reader Moran knows his product. Like many cereals, this one
can be difficult (impossible?) to find. However, you can order it
from the company at 1-800-725-7866 or www.hotralston.com. A case of
six 20-ounce boxes is $14.32. Ralston has been making its milled
wheat cereal since 1896. During the '30s and '40s, cowboy Tom Mix
was the radio spokesman, when the box boasted the familiar
red-and-white checkerboard trim. Today's cereal cooks in a flash or
is microwavable. You can also use the cereal to make cinnamon
crunch muffins. The recipe is on the box.
</P>
<P>
   Q: While on our honeymoon in Australia, my husband got hooked on
Tim Tam cookies, made by Arnott's, which is owned by Campbell Soup.
We have tried everywhere, including Harry's, to find them, with no
luck. Are they sold anywhere in the States?
</P>
<P>
   _ Daphne
</P>
<P>
   Freeman,
</P>
<P>
   Buford, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: At first we thought a trip to Australia was in order. Then we
did a bit of digging and found Tim Tams in our own back yard _
Marietta. You can order those Arnott's cookies (also called
biscuits) through the Australian Catalogue Co., 1165 Allgood Road,
Marietta (678-560-6384). A package of 11 cookies is $3.60. The
company's Web site is www.aussiecatalog.com.
</P>
<P>
   What makes these treats irresistible to chocoholics? Try two
chocolate biscuits filled with chocolate cream and coated with milk
chocolate. Tim Tams are also available with a caramel filling.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
