   Israel's announcement Wednesday that it would halt the sale of
sophisticated radar technology to mainland China was an indication
that the talks were headed in a positive direction, and that
Israel, at least was in a concessionary mode.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton had repeatedly urged Barak to scrap the planned $250
