<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-12 20:21 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0435 &Cx1f; tab-z
u k BC-OPED-IPO-CAMP-BOROWIT     07-12 0508
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OPED-IPO-CAMP-BOROWITZ-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STARTUPS IN THE PINES 
</HEADLINE>
   (New York Times OpEd for Thursday, July 13, and thereafter.)  
 ATTENTION EDITORS: This article is for use by clients of The New
York Times Syndicate's OPED news service. For more information
about purchasing this article as a separate-buy' _ or becoming a
client of the OPED news service _ contact one of the New York Times
Syndicate sales representatives listed at the end of the text.)  
 By ANDY BOROWITZ    
 c.2000 New York Times    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dear Mom and Dad,
</P>
<P>
   Camp is AWESOME!!! There's this really cool girl named Stephanie
in my cabin, and guess what _ she has a really, REALLY cool idea
for a Web site. We're going to call it lettersfromcamp.com, and
we're going to offer consulting services for kids writing letters
from camp on a paid subscription basis and make TONS of money.
</P>
<P>
   Pet Pumpkin for me!!!
</P>
<P>
   Love, Amy
</P>
<P>
   Dear Mom and Dad,
</P>
<P>
   It rained all day today, but that was OK with me and Stephanie,
because we were meeting with our money people. Our first round of
financing went really, REALLY well _ we raised $15 million!!!
That's, like, 10 million weeks' allowance!!! We're thinking of
adding an e-commerce component _ bug spray, duffel bags, etc.
</P>
<P>
   Tell Pumpkin I'm going to be really, REALLY rich!!!
</P>
<P>
   Love, Amy
</P>
<P>
   Dear Mom and Dad,
</P>
<P>
   Today while we were playing Capture the Flag, Stephanie brought
along her Palm VII to check our stock price after the IPO, and we
closed at $178 a share. My counselor, Sherrie, said it was the
biggest opening-day pop in the ENTIRE cabin!
</P>
<P>
   Say hi to the dog.
</P>
<P>
   Love, Amy
</P>
<P>
   Dear Mom and Dad,
</P>
<P>
   Our money people are REALLY mean!!! They said we weren't turning
a profit and probably never would! Stephanie told them we were
delivering eyeballs, but they were like, eyeballs are a dime a
dozen. And we were like, SOR-RY!!!
</P>
<P>
   Got to go. We're trying to get some second-round financing from
the Philippines. Hi dog.
</P>
<P>
   Love, Amy
</P>
<P>
   Dear Mom and Dad,
</P>
<P>
   Our stock went down to 45 cents, and Stephanie and I had to go
into Chapter 11 and fire everyone in the cabin. It is SO UNFAIR!!!
Our money people wouldn't even let us TELL them about the awesome
Super Bowl ads we came up with!
</P>
<P>
   I hate, hate, HATE camp!!! I miss, miss, MISS Pumpkin!!! PLEASE
TAKE ME HOME!!!!
</P>
<P>
   Love, Amy
</P>
<P>
   (Andy Borowitz is the author of ``The Trillionaire Next Door.'')
</P>
<P>
