 PERSONALS: Secrets of a Ravishing Beauty 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``If I'm at home,''  &UR; Joan Collins  &LR; told the Telegraph of London,
``I'll often open a can of sardines, because sardines are terribly
good for you. Sardines contain a tremendous amount of DNA, which is
one of the things one should eat a lot of.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; THE NADER STARS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Ralph Nader  &LR; called the Washington Post and complained that
 &UR; Al &LR; 
 &UR; Gore &LR;  has been calling Nader's celebrity endorsers and trying to
get them to change their minds.
</P>
<P>
   Nader didn't reveal the names of those who told him they'd been
called by the veep because he said they didn't want publicity. But
the list of well-known Nader endorsers includes
 &UR; Susan Sarandon &LR; ,  &UR; Bonnie Raitt &LR; ,  &UR; Phil Donahue &LR; ,  &UR; Eddie &LR;   &UR; Vedder &LR; 
and
 &UR; Willie Nelson &LR; .  &UR; Paul &LR;   &UR; Newman &LR;  also has donated money to Nader.
</P>
<P>
   Nader told the Post he wouldn't try to steal anyone else's
supporters. ``It would never occur to me to wean someone away.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Richard Simmons  &LR; turned 52 Wednesday, July 12, and celebrated
on his Web site with the image of him walking down a wedding aisle
with a giant carrot. This is supposed to symbolize saying ``I do''
to good health.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Michael Jackson &LR;  is being sued by Beverly Hills jeweler
 &UR; David Orgell  &LR; for keeping a $1.45 million Vacheron Constantine
diamond watch for four months and then returning it scratched and
refusing to pay for it. The jeweler said Jackson had bought the
watch, but ``it's our custom and practice not to ask for payment on
the spot, as that would be insulting to clients.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Michael Douglas &LR;  and  &UR; Catherine Zeta-Jones &LR;  have completed
work on their prenuptial agreement, says MSNBC, which reports that
she's to get $3 million for every year they stay together.
</P>
<P>
   _ Suffering for beauty: When a flock of Victoria's Secret models
went to Cannes recently for a Fashion 2000 show, reports New York
magazine,  &UR; Aurelie Claudel &LR;  was so mobbed that she dropped her
3-pound Pomeranian, breaking the dog's leg. It wore a cast for the
rest of the festival.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
