<HEADLINE>
USC TO HIRE EX-WAVES ASSISTANT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ Former Pepperdine assistant coach Damon Archibald
is expected to be hired as an assistant coach at USC.
</P>
<P>
   Archibald will replace Paul Mokeski, who resigned last month to
become head coach of the Kansas City Knights of the American
Basketball Association. The Agoura resident is the son of former
Utah coach Lynn Archibald and played basketball at Boise State.
</P>
<P>
   Before working last season at Pepperdine, Archibald spent two
seasons at Fresno State as an assistant. &QL;
</P>
