<SLUG> BC-SOUTHERN-STOCK-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KC SOUTHERN STOCK CLIMBS ON DAY BEFORE SPINOFF OF FINANCIAL UNIT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RANDOLPH HEASTER  
 c. 1999 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Kansas City Southern Industries Inc. saw its
stock price surge on its final trading day as a railroad and
financial services company. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City Southern closed Wednesday at $92.94 a share, up
$2.50 in heavy trading on the New York Stock Exchange. Earlier in
the day, the stock reached a one-year high of $95.75 a share before
falling back. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In after-hours trading Wednesday, Kansas City Southern's stock
climbed further to $93.75 a share. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Analysts said Kansas City Southern's stock responded to merger
activity in the financial services sector and the pending spinoff
of its Stilwell Financial Inc. unit. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Boosting stocks of several asset management companies Wednesday
was news that UBS AG had bid to acquire PaineWebber Group Inc. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   At the close of trading Wednesday, Kansas City Southern spun off
Stilwell Financial into a separately traded public company.
Stilwell, whose holdings include the fast-growing Janus Capital
Corp. mutual fund group, will begin trading regularly today on the
New York Stock Exchange under the symbol SV. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Landon H. Rowland, Kansas City Southern's chairman and
Stilwell's chairman and chief executive officer, is expected to
ring the bell to open trading on the stock exchange today. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City Southern stockholders of record on June 28 are
receiving two shares of Stilwell for each Kansas City Southern
share. In addition, shares of Kansas City Southern are undergoing a
1-for-2 reverse split. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   An investor who owned 100 shares of Kansas City Southern will
receive 200 Stilwell shares and 50 Kansas City Southern shares
after the spinoff. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The two companies will report their second-quarter earnings
separately. Stilwell is expected to issue its latest financial
results on July 21 and Kansas City Southern on July 26, said Bill
Galligan, a Kansas City Southern spokesman. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
